5. “It will make transactions noticeably faster.”⚡️

Proof-of-Stake allows blocks to be produced only ~10% more frequently than PoW. 

It also introduces the concept of transaction finality which bolsters security, but this does not translate to noticeably faster transactions.

4.“Staking APR will increase by 200% after the Merge”

It is anticipated that the APR for $ETH staking will increase after the Merge. However, a tripling of the APR rate is unlikely. 

An increase of approximately 50% from the base issuance APR as of June, 2022 is more realistic.

3. “Staked $ETH can be withdrawn once the Merge occurs.” 

Staked $ETH will continue to be locked on the Beacon Chain for another 6-12 months until the Shanghai upgrade -- the next major upgrade after the Merge.

2. “It will cause #ETH downtime.”⌛️

The Merge will be triggered when the terminal total difficulty (TTD) hits 58750000000000000000000. 

Once this happens, the subsequent blocks will be built using PoS with ZERO downtime.

1. “The Merge reduces gas fees.”⛽️

This is the elephant in the room. Let’s address it. 

The network demand relative to the capacity of the network determines the gas fees. 

The Merge does not expand the network capacity and therefore, will not lower gas fees.
